problem: What is the 453rd digit to the right of the decimal point in the decimal expansion of $\frac{6}{13}$?
solution: The decimal representation of $\frac{6}{13}$ is $0.\overline{461538}$, which repeats every 6 digits. Since 453 divided by 6 has a remainder of 3, the 453rd digit is the same as the third digit after the decimal point, which is $\boxed{1}$.
